What you used AI for
I used Perplexity as a helper for design and boilerplate to speed up the initial scaffolding, not as the final authority.

Where it helped
It helped me explore options like optimistic locking, the outbox pattern, and their related trade‑offs. It supported my decision‑making by clarifying the requirements and implications of different approaches.

What you changed or improved
I added more fields at the entity level with future scalability in mind. I followed best practices such as using a custom validator instead of performing validation in the service layer. I implemented custom exceptions to return appropriate HTTP statuses and error messages. I used a transition map to validate transaction status changes instead of chaining if/else conditions. I also improved the code by following SOLID principles, making classes open for extension and closed for modification.